==English==
===Etymology===
From [[geo-]] + Greek [[στροφή]] ‘act of turning’ + [[-ic]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ʤɪəˈstrəʊfɪk/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-ad|geostrophic}}

# ([[Meteorology]]). Referring to the [[balance]], in the [[atmosphere]], between the horizontal [[coriolis force]]s and the [[horizonal pressure force]]s.
# ([[Meteorology]]). Relates to or [[arises]] from the [[deflective]] force exerted on the atmosphere due to the [[rotation]] of the [[earth]].

